Odontomachus LATREILLE, 1804
is a genus of the
Ponerinae ( BOLTON 2003 )
and contains 73 extant and three valid fossil species (
). It is widely distributed in tropical regions, with highest species numbers in the Neotropics and Malesia (see
).
